03/04/2006
VLORA, Albania -- One man was killed and four were injured after a bomb planted in a Mercedes exploded in the southwest Albanian town of Vlora on Saturday (1 April).
According to local police, the man who was killed was identified as Astrit Elmazi, 35, while the injured were children aged 13 to 15, who were playing near the parking lot where the explosion happened.
The local media reported that the police suspect two motivations for the blast -- revenge or drug trafficking.
(Focus - 03/04/06;
AP - 02/04/06)
